Classic issue — missing `base` path. GitHub Pages serves your site at `https://username.github.io/repo-name/`, but Vite builds with `/` as the base, so all asset paths like `/assets/index.js` 404.

Fix in `vite.config.ts`:

```ts
export default defineConfig({
  plugins: [react()],
  base: '/wc3-build-order-app/', // your repo name here
  server: {
    port: 3000,
  },
  build: {
    target: 'esnext',
  },
});
```

Replace `wc3-build-order-app` with your actual GitHub repo name. Then rebuild and redeploy.

